### trunc is a microbenchmark that times how long it takes to fault
### a number of sparse files and then truncate them. The primary
### intent is to stress basic page cache operations and not the
### underlying filesystem although the underlying filesystem may
### still matter if storage is reserved on-disk.
export MMTESTS="trunc"

